<start> ::= <BodyStructure>

<BodyStructure> ::= body_Link_CUBE.urdf <FaceSet>

A body may have attachments on one or more faces.
<FaceSet> ::= <>
            | <FaceAttachment> <FaceSet>

Each face attachment is defined separately so that the joint used is appropriate.
<FaceAttachment> ::= <FaceAttachment_BACK>
                   | <FaceAttachment_BOTTOM>
                   | <FaceAttachment_FRONT>
                   | <FaceAttachment_LEFT>
                   | <FaceAttachment_RIGHT>
                   | <FaceAttachment_TOP>

For each face, first the auxiliary sphere for that face is given,
then a choice is offered: either attach a new body or attach a limb.
<FaceAttachment_BACK> ::= sphere_auxiliar_Link_BACK.urdf <AttachmentChoice_BACK>
<FaceAttachment_BOTTOM> ::= sphere_auxiliar_Link_BOTTOM.urdf <AttachmentChoice_BOTTOM>
<FaceAttachment_FRONT> ::= sphere_auxiliar_Link_FRONT.urdf <AttachmentChoice_FRONT>
<FaceAttachment_LEFT> ::= sphere_auxiliar_Link_LEFT.urdf <AttachmentChoice_LEFT>
<FaceAttachment_RIGHT> ::= sphere_auxiliar_Link_RIGHT.urdf <AttachmentChoice_RIGHT>
<FaceAttachment_TOP> ::= sphere_auxiliar_Link_TOP.urdf <AttachmentChoice_TOP>

For each face, the attachment choice is between a body attachment (using the appropriate joint)
or a limb attachment (using a limb joint).
<AttachmentChoice_BACK> ::= <B_Joint_BACK> <BodyStructure>
                           | <L_Joint> <LimbChain>
<AttachmentChoice_BOTTOM> ::= <B_Joint_BOTTOM> <BodyStructure>
                             | <L_Joint> <LimbChain>
<AttachmentChoice_FRONT> ::= <B_Joint_FRONT> <BodyStructure>
                            | <L_Joint> <LimbChain>
<AttachmentChoice_LEFT> ::= <B_Joint_LEFT> <BodyStructure>
                           | <L_Joint> <LimbChain>
<AttachmentChoice_RIGHT> ::= <B_Joint_RIGHT> <BodyStructure>
                            | <L_Joint> <LimbChain>
<AttachmentChoice_TOP> ::= <B_Joint_TOP> <BodyStructure>
                          | <L_Joint> <LimbChain>

Body joints for each face (choose one)
<B_Joint_BACK> ::= B_joint_revolute_BACK.urdf | B_joint_continuous_BACK.urdf | B_joint_fixed_BACK.urdf
<B_Joint_BOTTOM> ::= B_joint_revolute_BOTTOM.urdf | B_joint_continuous_BOTTOM.urdf | B_joint_fixed_BOTTOM.urdf
<B_Joint_FRONT> ::= B_joint_revolute_FRONT.urdf | B_joint_continuous_FRONT.urdf | B_joint_fixed_FRONT.urdf
<B_Joint_LEFT> ::= B_joint_revolute_LEFT.urdf | B_joint_continuous_LEFT.urdf | B_joint_fixed_LEFT.urdf
<B_Joint_RIGHT> ::= B_joint_revolute_RIGHT.urdf | B_joint_continuous_RIGHT.urdf | B_joint_fixed_RIGHT.urdf
<B_Joint_TOP> ::= B_joint_revolute_TOP.urdf | B_joint_continuous_TOP.urdf | B_joint_fixed_TOP.urdf

Limb joints (for attaching limbs to a face or extending a limb)
<L_Joint> ::= L_joint_revolute.urdf 
            | L_joint_continuous.urdf 
            | L_joint_fixed.urdf 
            | L_joint_revolute_horizontal.urdf

A limb chain is built from a limb element, with optional extensions.
<LimbChain> ::= <Limb> <LimbExtension>
<LimbExtension> ::= <> 
                  | <L_Joint> <LimbChain>

Limbs: choose one of the types.
<Limb> ::= <Big_Link> 
         | <Small_Link> 
         | <Wheel_Link>
<Big_Link> ::= limb_Link.urdf
<Small_Link> ::= limb_Link_Small.urdf
<Wheel_Link> ::= wheel_link.urdf